
Date: Thu, 4 Nov 2010 10:57:24 +0100 (CET)
From: advisory@...ridge.ch
To: bugtraq@...urityfocus.com
Subject: BBcode XSS in MiniBB

Vulnerability ID: HTB22670
Reference: http://www.htbridge.ch/advisory/bbcode_xss_in_minibb.html
Product: MiniBB
Vendor: MiniBB.com ( http://www.minibb.com/ ) 
Vulnerable Version: 2.5
Vendor Notification: 21 October 2010 
Vulnerability Type: XSS (Cross Site Scripting)
Status: Not Fixed, Vendor Alerted, Awaiting Vendor Response
Risk level: Medium 
Credit: High-Tech Bridge SA - Ethical Hacking & Penetration Testing (http://www.htbridge.ch/) 

Vulnerability Details:
User can execute arbitrary JavaScript code within the vulnerable application.
BBcode isn't properly sanitized. This can be used to post arbitrary script code.
Successful exploitation of this vulnerability could result in a compromise of the application, theft of cookie-based authentication credentials, disclosure or modification of sensitive data.

An attacker can use browser to exploit this vulnerability.
BBcode Example:

[imgs=http://nosuch.gif][url=http://onerror=javascript:alert(/XSS/);"']123[/url][/imgs]


